#so here we need to really know this !


1. the URL

this is broken up into different paths !

this is where the request goes !
this tells python

send the request to this location !

https://          = protocol
pokeapi.co       = API server/domain
/api/v2/pokemon/pikachu = endpoint/resource path



2. method --> the action you want

GET    = read/retrieve data
POST   = create/send new data
PUT    = replace/update data
PATCH  = partially update data
DELETE = delete data

for example 1

requests.get(url)
I want to read data from this URL.



for example 2

requests.post(url, json=data)
I want to send new data to this URL.




3. HEADERS --> this is metadata !
extra information about the request !

Authorization = login/API token
Content-Type = what format you are sending
Accept = what format you want back





4. ERROR AND VALIDATION ERRORS

400 = bad input from client
401 = not logged in / missing auth
403 = logged in but not allowed
404 = resource not found
409 = conflict with current state
422 = validation failed
500 = server crashed / unexpected backend error





5. what is seed data ?

starter data you put into your app/database so the project has something to work with





6. what are roots ?

A route is a URL path your API listens for.
When someone visits this path with this HTTP method,
run this Python function.









